124 TEST(PioneerPacket, TwoBytes_Vector_Commands)
125 {
126  PioneerPacket pac;
127  std::vector<bool> f_byte(8,0);
128  f_byte[0] = 1;
129  f_byte[2] = 1;
130  std::vector<bool> s_byte(4,0);
131  s_byte[1] = 1;
132  s_byte[3] = 1;
133  pac.command(DIGOUT, f_byte, s_byte);
134  EXPECT_EQ(pac[0],0xFA);
135  EXPECT_EQ(pac[1],0xFB);
136  EXPECT_EQ(pac[2],0x06);
137  EXPECT_EQ(pac[3],0x1E);
138  EXPECT_EQ(pac[4],0x3B);
139  EXPECT_EQ(pac[5],0x05);
140  EXPECT_EQ(pac[6],0x0A);
141  EXPECT_EQ(pac[7],0x23);
142  EXPECT_EQ(pac[8],0x45);
143 }

171 TEST(PioneerPacket, Get_Unsigned_Integer_At_Accessor)
172 {
173  PioneerPacket pac;
174  pac.command(HOSTBAUD, 40000); // Value larger than 32767
175  EXPECT_EQ(pac.at(0), 6); // Size of packet
176  EXPECT_EQ(pac.at(1), HOSTBAUD); // The command
177  EXPECT_EQ(pac.at(2), ARGINT); // The data type
178  int value, index;
179  index = pac.getUnsignedAt(3, value);
180  EXPECT_EQ(value, 40000); // The Integer
181  EXPECT_EQ(index, 5); // The index of the next values
182 }

197 TEST(PioneerPacket, Get_String_At_Length_Accessor)
198 {
199  PioneerPacket pac;
200  pac.command(TTY2, "TEST");
201  EXPECT_EQ(pac.at(0), 9); // Size of packet
202  EXPECT_EQ(pac.at(1), TTY2); // The command
203  EXPECT_EQ(pac.at(2), ARGSTR); // The data type
204  EXPECT_EQ(pac.at(3), 4); // The size of the string
205  std::string value;
206  int index;
207  index = pac.getStringAt(4, 4, value);
208  EXPECT_STREQ(value.c_str(),"TEST"); // The String
209  EXPECT_EQ(index, 9);
210 }

227 TEST(PioneerPacket, Get_Bool_Vector_At_Accessor)
228 {
229  PioneerPacket pac;
230  pac.command(ENABLE, 21); // Just for testing
231  std::vector<bool> value;
232  int index;
233  index = pac.getBoolVectorAt(3, value);
234  EXPECT_EQ(index, 4);
235  EXPECT_EQ(value.size(), 8);
236  EXPECT_EQ(value[0], 1);
237  EXPECT_EQ(value[1], 0);
238  EXPECT_EQ(value[2], 1);
239  EXPECT_EQ(value[3], 0);
240  EXPECT_EQ(value[4], 1);
241  EXPECT_EQ(value[5], 0);
242  EXPECT_EQ(value[6], 0);
243  EXPECT_EQ(value[7], 0);
244 }
